  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Home Environment Safety Response Interconnect\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Home Environment Safety Response Interconnect\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Published personal-health bridge bus that composes home environment safety, food access, adolescent behavioral health, social isolation, and fall-safety context into a compact fan-out lane for urgent housing safety response, utility/housing resource support, health-hazard behavioral follow-up, and stable monitoring. PE owns source composition and writes the compact input lane; RE evaluates this machine as ordinary vector state.\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- unsafe-housing-bit (index 0):\n- utility-failure-bit (index 1):\n- health-hazard-risk-bit (index 2):\n- environment-safe-bit (index 3):\n- food-crisis-bit (index 4):\n- food-insecure-bit (index 5):\n- food-assistance-needed-bit (index 6):\n- food-secure-bit (index 7):\n- adolescent-crisis-risk-bit (index 8):\n- adolescent-behavioral-concern-bit (index 9):\n- adolescent-elevated-stress-bit (index 10):\n- adolescent-mental-health-ok-bit (index 11):\n- severe-isolation-bit (index 12):\n- social-withdrawal-bit (index 13):\n- isolation-risk-bit (index 14):\n- socially-connected-bit (index 15):\n- fall-unsafe-tier-bit (index 16):\n- fall-high-confidence-bit (index 17):\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- URGENT_HOUSING_SAFETY_RESPONSE (RED) -> action: Route urgent housing safety response, care coordination, family stabilization, utility/rental assistance, and built-space incident follow-up.\n- UTILITY_HOUSING_RESOURCE_SUPPORT (AMBER) -> action: Route LIHEAP/utility assistance, rental support, case routing, and family resource support.\n- HEALTH_HAZARD_BEHAVIORAL_FOLLOWUP (AMBER) -> action: Route air/water quality, adolescent behavioral, maternal-child, and care-coordination follow-up before crisis escalation.\n- ENVIRONMENT_STABLE_MONITORING (GREEN) -> action: Continue lightweight built-space, family routine, and water-access monitoring.",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
